DefinedTerms.Corporate Governance:
In relation to:
(a)	a Reporting Entity, means the:
(i)	nature, constitution or functions of the organs of the Reporting Entity;
(ii)	manner in which organs of the Reporting Entity conduct themselves;
(iii)	requirements imposed on organs of the Reporting Entity;
(iv)	relationship between the different organs of the Reporting Entity; and
(v)	relationship between the organs of the Reporting Entity and the members of the Reporting Entity or holders of the Issuer's Securities; and
(b)	all other cases, means the principles prescribed in MKT 9.2.3 to 9.2.9.
